@page "/docs/changelog"
@namespace Lumeo.Docs.Pages.Docs

<PageTitle>Lumeo Changelog — Release Notes and Version History</PageTitle>

<Container MaxWidth="3xl" Padding="0" Center="false">
<Stack Gap="10">

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <Heading Level="1" Size="3xl">Changelog</Heading>
        <Lumeo.Text Size="base" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
            All notable changes to Lumeo are documented here. Each release groups changes into Added, Improved, and Fixed categories.
        </Lumeo.Text>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v4.2.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v4.2.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">July 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>DataGrid column resize</strong> — always-visible hover handle, a guideline that tracks the exact cell edge (min/max clamp, horizontal scroll, first column, RTL), double-click auto-fit to content width, and keyboard resizing on the focused handle that never scrolls the page.</li>
            <li><strong>DataGrid column reorder</strong> — one pointer engine for mouse/touch/pen with live sibling-shift animation, glide-settle on drop, Escape glide-back, and locked/pinned columns preserved in preview and commit.</li>
            <li><strong>DataGrid row reorder</strong> — handle-only vertical dragging on the same engine; expanded detail rows travel with their parent as one band; commits resolve by stable row key. Scoped to flat, non-virtualized grids.</li>
            <li><strong>Robustness</strong> — a per-grid arbiter serializes every mutating gesture and is held until the commit (including awaited <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">OnColumnResize</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">OnRowReorder</code> handlers) fully completes; every commit runs through one canonical validation path whose rejection always clears drag transforms. New APIs: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ReorderColumnByIdAsync</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ReorderRowByKeyAsync</code>; strings localized in all 14 locales. Per-move work stays in JavaScript (~0.004&#8211;0.007&#160;ms per move).</li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v4.1.2 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge Variant="Badge.BadgeVariant.Secondary">v4.1.2</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">July 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>Icons</strong> — the last Blazicons remnants are removed everywhere (docs interop packages, comparison surfaces, CSS compat rule, samples); the icon page and customizer are first-party-only, and DynamicIcon demos generic third-party interop via inline <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">IconSource</code>.</li>
            <li><strong>CLI</strong> — the preset icon catalog is first-party only (all variant ids accepted); legacy names in stored presets normalize through one pre-write gate (rewrite or warn-and-skip), and <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">--dry-run</code> previews exactly what apply would write.</li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v4.1.1 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge Variant="Badge.BadgeVariant.Secondary">v4.1.1</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">July 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>TreeView</strong> — parent-node selection fixed (#350: identity-based, value-less containers no longer co-select) and hardened over a 21-round review loop incl. a structural rebuild: UI state is tree-owned and survives controlled rebuilds. New: clicking a parent row selects AND expands it (VS Code pattern, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ExpandOnRowClick</code> opt-out), tri-state checkboxes derive from seeded state on first render, and the chevron is visually integrated into the row.</li>
            <li><strong>Consent</strong> — GDPR hardening: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">PolicyVersion</code> re-prompts on mismatch with proof-of-consent (timestamp + version, fail-closed on malformed/versionless records), equal-weight layer-1 buttons, and a reopen surface pattern.</li>
            <li><strong>Charts</strong> — self-hosting story completed: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">window.lumeoCdn</code> plugin override keys + per-chart <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">EChartsSource</code> forwarding, and the docs load zero third-party chart assets before consent.</li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v4.1.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v4.1.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">July 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Lumeo.Text Size="base" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
            The stable roll-up of the <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">4.1.0-preview.1 … .15</code> line plus the merged shadcn-parity campaign. <strong>Additive and opt-in</strong> — no API-signature breaks from 4.0.x except the icon-package decouple. Headlined by a <strong>first-party icon family</strong> (16 trimmable packs), <strong><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">dotnet new</code> templates</strong>, and a <strong>shadcn parity campaign</strong> hardened over ten review rounds. A few behaviour changes to know before upgrading: declarative <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Dialog</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">AlertDialog</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Drawer</code> now animate their close by default (opt out with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">PlayExitAnimation="false"</code>); <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ToggleGroup Orientation="Vertical"</code> now lays out vertically; Sidebar <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Ctrl/Cmd+B</code> is registered as the default toggle (editor-safe). Blazicons is fully decoupled — <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Icon.Svg</code> and friends now take <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Lumeo.IconSource</code>.
        </Lumeo.Text>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>First-party icon family</strong> — 16 trimmable packs (~51,000 icons, all <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">IsTrimmable</code>): Lucide, Tabler(+Filled), Phosphor ×6 weights, Heroicons, Remix, Bootstrap, Iconoir, Material Symbols, Fluent. New <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">IconSource</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">SvgGlyph</code> renderer, a searchable <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">/icons</code> gallery, and customizer live icon-library switching.</li>
                <li><strong><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">dotnet new lumeo-app</code></strong> (styled Blazor WASM starter, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">--auth demo|none|oidc</code>) and <strong><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">dotnet new lumeo-fullstack</code></strong> (client + ASP.NET Core API, Identity, EF Core/PostgreSQL, Scalar, MailHog, docker-compose).</li>
                <li><strong>shadcn parity</strong> — <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">data-*</code> styling hooks on nine components; native form participation (Checkbox/Switch bubble inputs with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Name</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Value</code>); Menubar checkbox/radio/group/inset/destructive/shortcut + typeahead; controlled <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">NavigationMenu</code> (<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Value</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ValueChanged</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">DelayDuration</code>); exit animations + <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">data-state</code> on the menu-style overlays; Chart <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">AccessibilityLayer</code> (capped SR table); AgentMessageList scroll button / empty state / Markdown export and AgentMessage actions + branch nav.</li>
                <li><strong>Component APIs</strong> — <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">TabsVariant.Underline</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">AvatarShape.Themed</code>, DataGrid header-level pin control + programmatic column visibility, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">TooltipContent.Align</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">FullWidth</code> on the picker family, Maps cluster/interop APIs, and more.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Changed</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>Theme-radius wave</strong> — ~75 hardcoded roundings across ~40 components now follow the <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">--radius</code> token; every stock theme renders <strong>pixel-identical</strong> to 4.0, only sharp themes square off.</li>
                <li><strong>Behaviour</strong> — declarative overlay close animates by default (<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">PlayExitAnimation</code> opt-out); <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ToggleGroup</code> vertical lays out vertically; Sidebar <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Ctrl/Cmd+B</code> default (editor-safe); collapsed rail is 16px narrower with shadcn-1:1 timing.</li>
                <li><strong>Docs</strong> — landing perf rebuild (Lighthouse mobile 36 → 97), new API/guide pages for every wave, and a currency pass.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Fixed</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>Overlay exit saga (B10/B11)</strong> — service-opened Dialog/Drawer/AlertDialog and declarative Sheets now animate out reliably (Radix Presence port; backdrop + panel finish in sync); exiting overlays are <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">inert</code> while modal backdrops shield through the exit; the Sheet backdrop catches click-outside again.</li>
                <li><strong>DataGrid</strong> — column pinning reorders columns in DOM order (right-pin works), the drag hot-path no longer round-trips to .NET (~198 ms → ~0.02 ms/event), <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Compact</code> genuinely tightens rows, cleaner facet filters.</li>
                <li><strong>Popovers</strong> — fixed-position surfaces no longer open offset inside transformed ancestors (double containing-block fold); popovers-in-dialogs and over-viewport Select/Combobox lists fixed.</li>
                <li><strong>Avatar</strong> Square/Themed initials, <strong>Tooltip</strong> click-dismiss + edge-clamped arrow, template scaffolds, and a timing-test deflake.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v4.0.1 - v4.0.4 (patch series) -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge Variant="Badge.BadgeVariant.Secondary">v4.0.4</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">July 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>Tooltip</strong> — a Tooltip-wrapped clickable trigger no longer sticks open after a mouse click: focus-driven opening is now gated on the browser's <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">:focus-visible</code> signal, so keyboard focus still opens the tooltip immediately while click-focus does not.</li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge Variant="Badge.BadgeVariant.Secondary">v4.0.3</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">July 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>Sidebar</strong> — the menu-button label fade now matches the container's collapse/expand transition exactly (duration, delay and easing, both directions) instead of finishing at 150ms while the rail kept moving until 300ms.</li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge Variant="Badge.BadgeVariant.Secondary">v4.0.2</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">July 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>DataGrid</strong> — ServerMode grouping no longer visually rebuilds the grid on expand/collapse: regrouping now works from the raw server page instead of the previous regroup's filtered output (which could even wipe grouping entirely with <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">GroupsExpandedByDefault="false"</code>).</li>
            <li><strong>Select</strong> — Multiple-mode trigger tags resolve the item's rendered label instead of echoing the raw value; an explicit <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">SelectTrigger</code> ChildContent now always wins; wrapped tag rows no longer mis-center the chevron/clear icons.</li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge Variant="Badge.BadgeVariant.Secondary">v4.0.1</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">July 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
            <li><strong>DataGrid</strong> — ServerMode + grouping: manually collapsed groups keep their expand state across page turns, sorts, filters and searches (state is remembered per group key for the life of the grid), and <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">OnServerRequest</code> now receives the actual runtime grouping instead of the static <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">GroupBy</code> parameter.</li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v4.0.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v4.0.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">June 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Lumeo.Text Size="base" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
            The 4.0.0 major release. A Radix / Base UI / shadcn <strong>parity audit</strong> (accessibility, RTL, theming, the FormGenerator, MCP/CLI — additive and opt-in) plus a library-wide <strong>correctness hardening</strong> pass: an adversarial battle-test of all 164 components that fixed ~355 confirmed bugs, each with a bUnit regression test (suite 4,983 green). No API-signature breaks — the major bump signals scope and a handful of behaviour changes (see Changed and <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">MIGRATION.md</code>). Headlined by the CLI's NuGet-free standalone eject.
        </Lumeo.Text>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>CLI — NuGet-free "standalone" eject</strong>: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">lumeo init --standalone</code> (or <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">lumeo eject</code> on an existing project) makes <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">add</code> vendor each component <strong>plus the shared runtime it needs</strong> (vendored once into <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">_LumeoRuntime/</code>) as source, so the project builds and runs with <strong>zero Lumeo/satellite <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">PackageReference</code></strong>. Satellites vendor their source + JS too. Validated by building all 164 components standalone (164/164 green).</li>
                <li><strong>DirectionProvider</strong>: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">&lt;DirectionProvider Direction="LayoutDirection.Rtl"&gt;</code> sets the native <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">dir</code> and cascades it so descendant layout mirrors for RTL.</li>
                <li><strong>Tabs</strong>: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">IconReveal</code> — inactive triggers collapse to icon-only; the active trigger animates its label open next to the icon.</li>
                <li><strong>Composition / a11y parity</strong>: Card <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">CardTitle</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">CardDescription</code>, Avatar <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">StatusLabel</code>, Chart <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">AriaLabel</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">AsChild</code> on AlertDialog/Drawer triggers, and the public class-merge helper <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Lumeo.Cx</code>.</li>
                <li><strong>Forms / data</strong>: DataTable <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ItemKey</code> (selection survives async reloads), RadioGroup <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Name</code> for native form submission, and live re-init of Gantt's <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Readonly</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">TodayHighlight</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">BarHeight</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ColumnWidth</code>.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Improved</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>RTL</strong>: migrated the library's directional Tailwind utilities to logical ones (<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ml-→ms-</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">left-→start-</code>, …) — identical in LTR, mirrored in RTL.</li>
                <li><strong>FormField a11y</strong>: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">aria-describedby</code> (help/error) now reaches every form control, not just Input; single-focus controls adopt the field's <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ControlId</code> so <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">&lt;label for&gt;</code> resolves.</li>
                <li><strong>Accessibility</strong>: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">aria-current</code> on active Sidebar/Scrollspy links; overlay entry animations honour <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">prefers-reduced-motion</code>; Cascader arrow-key roving; Menubar roles; scroll-lock compensates for scrollbar width (no page shift on open).</li>
                <li><strong>LumeoFormGenerator</strong>: richer type coverage (TimeOnly/TimeSpan, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">List&lt;string&gt;</code>, MultilineText, Phone/Url), validation mapping (<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">[Range]</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">[StringLength]</code>), and <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">[Display(Order)]</code> ordering.</li>
                <li><strong>MCP</strong>: type-bound enum validation, a new <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">lumeo_get_a11y</code> tool, and per-component test-coverage + <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">[EditorRequired]</code> surfaced.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Changed</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>Theme</strong>: the entire colour palette (base + all 8 themes, 878 tokens) migrated from HSL to <strong>OKLCH</strong> — exact 1:1, brand identity unchanged, matching Tailwind v4 / current shadcn.</li>
                <li><strong>Behaviour</strong>: removable Badge is now fully controlled (data-driven, no optimistic self-hide); Progress/Gauge/RingProgress clamp out-of-range values and report <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">aria-busy</code> when indeterminate.</li>
                <li><strong>State survival</strong>: selection / checked / expand-collapse / active index / page / search / scroll / in-progress edit state now survives a same-content data refresh, an empty→refill async load, and unrelated parent re-renders.</li>
                <li><strong>Roving order</strong>: RadioGroup / ToggleGroup / Segmented / Stepper / Splitter / Steps / Accordion track live DOM order for arrow-key navigation after a keyed reorder.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Fixed</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>Battle-test campaign</strong> — ~355 bugs across all 164 components, each with a bUnit regression test: state-on-data-change, keyboard &amp; ARIA, edge data (empty/null/huge/out-of-range), lifecycle teardown (no <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">StateHasChanged</code> after dispose), and the keyed-reorder class.</li>
                <li><strong>Real-browser docs-QA</strong>: a render crash from a Razor comment placed between an element's attributes (Cascader, PdfViewer); an Input <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Type="file"</code> value crash; loose form-field layout (23 controls now render as one self-contained block); FormField + FormMessage rendering the error twice; Gauge value centring; ImageGallery grid collapse; a raw TagInput localization key.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v3.19.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v3.19.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">June 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Lumeo.Text Size="base" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
            Two P1 audit features — Drawer snap points and RichTextEditor accessibility. Additive and opt-in.
        </Lumeo.Text>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>Drawer (#218)</strong> vaul-style snap points: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">SnapPoints</code> + two-way <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">ActiveSnapPoint</code> — rests at fractional heights, drags between them, dismisses below the lowest.</li>
                <li><strong>Drawer (#218)</strong> velocity/flick dismiss (<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">SwipeDismissVelocity</code>, default 0.4 px/ms; 0 = distance-only).</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Improved</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>Drawer (#218)</strong> backdrop uses the <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">--color-overlay-backdrop</code> token (matches Sheet/Dialog).</li>
                <li><strong>RichTextEditor (#320)</strong> floating bubble toolbar is keyboard-operable (<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Alt+F10</code>, roving focus, Escape/Tab return to editor) and stays inside a modal focus trap.</li>
                <li><strong>RichTextEditor (#320)</strong> slash/mention listbox wires <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">aria-activedescendant</code> so screen readers announce the highlighted option.</li>
            </ul>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <!-- v3.18.0 -->
    <Stack Gap="4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <Badge>v3.18.0</Badge>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted">June 2026</Lumeo.Text>
        </div>

        <Lumeo.Text Size="base" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
            Bundled audit-backlog batch — the remaining cleanly-doable component gaps in one release. All additive and opt-in.
        </Lumeo.Text>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3" Size="sm" Class="font-semibold">Added</Heading>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>Pagination (#210)</strong> opt-in data-driven mode: <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">Page</code> + <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">TotalPages</code> (or <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">TotalItems</code>) render the full page list with sibling window + ellipsis and raise <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1 text-xs">PageChanged</code>.</li>
