                <li><strong><code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">OverlayOptions.MobileBreakpoint/MobileSheetSide/MobileSheetSize/MobileSwipeToClose</code></strong> — per-overlay responsive overrides. Below <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">MobileBreakpoint</code> (default 768px = Tailwind md) the <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">Mobile*</code> fields take precedence. <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">OverlayProvider</code> re-renders reactively on viewport crossing — sheet flips correctly when a tablet is rotated mid-flight.</li>
