            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm list-disc list-inside text-muted-foreground">
                <li><strong>OverlayService double-backdrop</strong> when consumers nested another <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;SheetContent&gt;</code> / <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;DialogContent&gt;</code> / <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;DrawerContent&gt;</code> inside their service-opened component. New <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">OverlayShellMarker</code> cascade — nested *Content components self-detect the host shell and pass children through. Both patterns now render exactly one backdrop. Regression test asserts <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">bg-black/80</code> appears exactly once.</li>
